-- Czech Stocks: Erste Group, New World Resources, Vienna Insurance
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-06-15T10:52:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-15/czech-stocks-erste-group-new-world-resources-vienna-insurance.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
rose 0.7 percent to 882.1 by 12:19 in Prague, paring its weekly
loss to 0.4 percent.  The following are among the most active  equities  in the
Czech market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Erste Group Bank AG (EBS)   of  Austria  added 0.6 percent
to 359 koruna and  Vienna Insurance Group AG (VIG)   climbed 4.1
percent to 755 koruna, a month high. Financial stocks were among
the best performers in Europe on optimism central banks will
step up economic stimulus.  New World Resources Plc (NWR)  , the biggest Czech coking-
coal producer, rose 4.6 percent to 102.51 koruna. Commodities
rallied, with Europe’s benchmark coal derivatives increasing 0.9
percent to $97 a metric ton in the Netherlands.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in  Prague  at 
